1
00:00:01,160 --> 00:00:02,360
DOCTOR: Appalapachia.

2
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:03,840
-AMY: Say it again?
-Appalapachia!

3
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:04,960
Appalapachia!

4
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:07,120
-Appalapachia.
-Appalapachia.

5
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:08,920
Appalapachia! What a beautiful word!

6
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,600
-Beautiful word, beautiful world.
-(AMY EXCLAIMS)

7
00:00:10,680 --> 00:00:11,760
Appalapachia!

8
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:13,240
Voted number two planet

9
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:18,040
in the Top Ten Greatest Destinations for
the Discerning Intergalactic Traveller.

10
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:20,200
-Why couldn't we go to number one?
-It's hideous!

11
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:22,920
Everyone goes to number one,
planet of the coffee shops.

12
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,520
Appalapachia. I give you sunsets,
spires, soaring silver colonnades.

13
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,200
I give you...

14
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:32,000
Doors.

15
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,200
Doors, yes. I give you doors.

16
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:38,160
But on the other side of those doors,
I give you sunsets, spires,

17
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:39,800
soaring silver colonnades.

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,360
Have you seen my phone?

19
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:43,000
-Your phone?
-Yeah.

20
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:45,320
Your mobile telephone.
I bring you to a paradise planet

21
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:49,000
two billion light years from Earth
and you want to update Twitter?

22
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,320
Sunsets, spires,
soaring silver colonnades.

23
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,640
It's a camera phone.

24
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:55,000
On the counter, by the DVDs.

25
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,200
Thank you.

26
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:59,240
-How do we get in?
-I don't know. Push a button.

27
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:08,520
Okay, so, rain check
on the soaring silver colonnades.

28
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:09,680
Yeah.

29
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,200
It's a magnifying glass.

30
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:24,200
-Hey, hey, it's locked.
-Yeah, push the button.

31
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:31,640
Rory?

32
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,200
Come on, Amy.

33
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,160
Great.

34
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:46,360
Where is she?

35
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:52,840
Where on wherever we are is my wife?

36
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:01,160
Rory, I think I've found her.

37
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:04,040
What do you mean you've found her?
Whoa! But...

38
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:07,720
No, but she's not here!

39
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,160
DOCTOR:
I can see her, but she's not here.

40
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:17,960
Where am I? In fact, where are you?

41
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,760
-(ELECTRIC BUZZING)
-Whoa!

42
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,280
Hands, hello, Hands.
Robot with hands, Rory.

43
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,240
HANDBOT: Welcome to
the Two-Streams Facility.

44
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:26,880
Will you be visiting long?

45
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,760
Uh, Doctor, something's happening.

46
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:31,720
Amy? Stay calm, stay still.

47
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,640
Time's gone wobbly.
I hate it when it does that.

48
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,440
Will you be visiting long?

49
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,440
Good question. A bit sinister.

50
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,560
What's the answer to not get us killed?

51
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,080
It's okay. I've got you. You're fine.

52
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,800
Will you be visiting long?

53
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,400
Doctor, a little help, Doctor.

54
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,640
And where have you been?

55
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,160
-Will you be visiting long?
-What do I tell it?

56
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,400
I've been here a week.

57
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,080
-A week?
-RORY: A week!

58
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,960
I'm so sorry.
Aha! Same room, different times.

59
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,320
Two different time streams running
parallel, but at different speeds.

60
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,720
Amy, you're in a faster time stream.

61
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,920
Doctor, it's going again!

62
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,800
-Doctor!
-Amy!

63
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,160
Doctor!

64
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:06,120
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

65
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:42,000
Ah, come on. Gotcha! There!

66
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,920
Stabilised. Settled. Shh.

67
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,280
Why has this got hands?

68
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:47,720
Organic skin.
Ultimate universal interface.

69
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,200
Grown and grafted, not born.

70
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,000
I mean, it's actually seeing
with its fingers, scanning the room.

71
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:54,160
-But why not just give it eyes?
-Will you be visiting long?

72
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,320
DOCTOR: As long as it takes.

73
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,640
Amy, what exactly did you do?

74
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:59,360
I just came in
and pressed a door button.

75
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:04,200
Oh! Amy, there are two buttons.
The green anchor and the red waterfall.

76
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,800
Which one did you push?

77
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:07,800
I pushed the red waterfall.

78
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,480
Great.

79
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,960
(DOCTOR TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

80
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,600
(EXHALES)

81
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,800
Amy?

82
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,960
Argh!

83
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,800
I pressed red waterfall
and she wasn't there!

84
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,640
DOCTOR: Okay, so,
you can't follow her directly...

85
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,280
No, it's never simple.

86
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,560
Did you hear that, Handbot?

87
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,720
She pressed the wrong button,
that's all.

88
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,120
We're aliens, we didn't know!

89
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:50,720
Statement rejected.

90
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:54,360
Appalapachia is under
planet-wide quarantine.

91
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:59,920
This is a Kindness Facility,
for those infected with Gen-7.

92
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,520
What?

93
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,000
DOCTOR: Gen-7.
RORY: Hmm?

94
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,320
The one-day plague.

95
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:09,600
-What, you get it for a day?
-No, you get it and you die in a day.

96
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:13,160
There are 40,000 residents
in the Two-Streams Facility.

97
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:17,880
Please remain in the sterile areas.
Visiting hours are now.

98
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:23,080
Sterile area, I'm safe.

99
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,160
What about me?

100
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:28,320
Gen-7 only affects two-hearted races,
like Appalapachians.

101
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,960
-And Time Lords.
-Yeah, like me.

102
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,560
Walk into that facility,
I'm dead in a day.

103
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,920
Time is faster on
Amy's side of the glass.

104
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,640
Uh, Amy, you said you'd been here
a week. What did you eat?

105
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,560
-Nothing. I wasn't hungry.
-No.

106
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,320
Because with that big waterfall,
time is compressed.

107
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,880
That's the point of the time glass.

108
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,440
It syncs up the two time streams
for visits.

109
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:46,160
You could be in here for a day.

110
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,320
And watch them
live out their entire lives.

111
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,680
And watch them grow old
in front of your eyes.

112
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,400
That's horrible!

113
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,320
No, Rory, it's kind.
You've got a choice.

114
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,440
Sit by their bedside for 24 hours
and watch them die

115
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,520
or sit in here for 24 hours
and watch them live.

116
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,480
Which would you choose?

117
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,880
Doctor?

118
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,400
Doctor, no, don't leave me.

119
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:17,160
I'm here, Amy. I'm right here.

120
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,200
Where are you? Am I looking at you?

121
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,520
Turn left, just a fraction.

122
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,160
Bit more. Stop.

123
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,920
That's it.

124
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,040
Eye to eye?

125
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,840
Eye to eye, do I.

126
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,720
Hello.

127
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,760
Amy, I'm taking the time glass
back to the Tardis.

128
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,960
Like SatNav, I can use it
to get a lock on you,

129
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,760
then smash through
using the Tardis to get you out.

130
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,480
Until then, you're on your own.

131
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:42,120
-Uh, what are you doing?
-Locking it onto Amy.

132
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,400
Small act of vandalism,
no one will mind.

133
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,520
-(ALARM BLARING)
-Ah!

134
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,760
That'll be the
small act of vandalism alarm.

135
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:48,080
Amy, I need you to go into the facility,
just for a bit.

136
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:50,920
Find somewhere safe to leave me a sign.
Remember, you are immune to Gen-7

137
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,080
but don't let them give you anything.
They don't know you're alien.

138
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:55,040
Their kindness will kill you. Now, go.

139
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,840
Rory, I love you.

140
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,880
Now, save me. Go on.

141
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,240
Ugh!

142
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,520
This is locked onto Amy permanently.

143
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,560
Play the signal into the console,
the Tardis will follow it.

144
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,960
Now, then, I know you're in here...

145
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,080
-(ALARM CLOCK RINGING)
-Um... Um...

146
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,280
Ha-ha!

147
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,600
-How do I look?
-Ridiculous.

148
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,160
Glasses are cool, see?

149
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,720
Oh, yes. Hello, handsome man.

150
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,080
Oh, hello.

151
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,120
Hello, Rorycam, huh?

152
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,680
-Oh, you can see what I see, right.
-You're breaking into Two-Streams.

153
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:46,560
Now, I can't go in there,
the Gen-7 will kill me. No regeneration.

154
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,360
You will be my eyes and ears.

155
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,720
-Rorycam. Rescue Amy. Got it.
-Mmm-hmm.

156
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,960
That's the spirit. Now, smashing through
a time wall could get a bit hairy.

157
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,400
-Is it safe?
-Don't know. Never tried. Best hold on.

158
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:16,440
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Welcome to the Two-Streams Facility.

159
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,480
Um, who are you and why can't I see you?

160
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:26,800
I am the interface between yourself and
the systems of the Two-Streams Facility.

161
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:30,480
I will be your guide, your teacher,
your friend.

162
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,360
Welcome to Two-Streams.

163
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,880
What is your name, please?

164
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,320
Amy, Amy Pond.

165
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:43,360
Welcome, Amy Pond.
I see you're travelling alone.

166
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,400
As a resident,
you will now have access to

167
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,440
all of the entertainment zones inside.

168
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:52,600
For a taste of adventure,
why not try the mountain zone,

169
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:56,440
and explore Appalapachia's famous
glass mirror mountains?

170
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,400
Or try our roller coaster zone.

171
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,080
Authentically model led on the famous
Warp-speed Death Ride

172
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,720
at Disneyland Cloumne.

173
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:08,080
All that you could wish for and more
is through the departure gate,

174
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:10,400
provided for you with kindness.

175
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:22,280
AUTOMATED VOICE: Unexpected visitor.
Welcome. Please seek assistance.

176
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,560
Hello? Hey! Oi, wait.

177
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:33,080
HANDBOT: You are carrying
unregistered bacteria.

178
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,920
Please let me help you.

179
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:40,920
No, I'm not from this world.
Your medicine will kill me.

180
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,400
Statement rejected.

181
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:47,240
Do not be alarmed. This is a kindness.

182
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,640
No, no, please, I hate you.

183
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,760
Secondary delivery system engaged.

184
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,800
Unauthorised infection on check in.

185
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:04,560
Version 223.

186
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,400
(ALARM BLARING)

187
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:15,800
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Unauthorised resident detected.

188
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,040
HANDBOT: This is a kindness.
Do not be alarmed.

189
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,120
This is a kindness.

190
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,280
(SCREAMING)

191
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,240
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Unauthorised resident detected.

192
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,440
Unauthorised resident detected.

193
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,320
No!

194
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:52,720
HANDBOT: This is a kindness.
Do not be alarmed.

195
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,080
This is a kindness.

196
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:00,200
This is a kindness. Do not be alarmed.

197
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,280
No residents detected.

198
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,520
No residents detected.

199
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,520
They didn't see me. They didn't see me.

200
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,880
(DOCTOR LAUGHING)

201
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,720
-Red Waterfall. We made it!
-Good on us.

202
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,920
How do we know that
we're in the same Red Waterfall as Amy?

203
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:45,000
Focus on the positive.
We locked onto Amy's time stream.

204
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,960
Eyes front, soldier.

205
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,160
Right, yes, sorry.

206
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:52,480
Appalapachians are the great
cultural scavengers, Rory.

207
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:55,280
This gallery's a scrapbook
of all their favourite places.

208
00:11:56,000 --> 00:12:00,080
Bit of Earth, bit of alien, bit of...

209
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,680
whatever the hell that is.

210
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,520
Interface?

211
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:15,400
AUTOMATED VOICE:
I am here, Amy Pond.

212
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,120
Shh! Turn that light off!

213
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,200
So, um, what is this? How does it work?

214
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,600
This is the gate.

215
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:27,840
From here, you may depart to any of
Two-Streams' entertainment zones.

216
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,040
Cinema.

217
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,240
(MUSIC PLAYING)

218
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,560
Aquarium.

219
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,640
(WATER GURGLING)

220
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,920
-Garden.
-Garden?

221
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,400
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

222
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,880
Why not?

223
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,160
Garden.

224
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,000
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

225
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,680
It's beautiful.

226
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,760
I mean, freaky hedges.

227
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:14,880
The perfect replica of a Shiel
Governor's mansion on Sheilama.

228
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:19,400
You really could spend a lifetime here.
Not that I'm going to.

229
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,600
-Interface?
-Amy Pond?

230
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:33,280
Listen, I need somewhere safe
to hide and wait for my friends.

231
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,320
Where in Two-Streams is safe?

232
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:38,240
Two-Streams is a safe,
nurturing environment.

233
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:42,480
You know what I mean. Where can I go
so the Handbots can't find me?

234
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,800
Okay. Um, before, I was saved
by a sort of vent,

235
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:49,560
and there was light and smoke,
and the Handbots couldn't see me.

236
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,880
Why not?

237
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:54,760
Okay, I will put it another way.
What were those vent thingies?

238
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:59,080
The vents channel the exhaust fumes
from the temporal engines

239
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,800
that hold the multiple time streams
in place.

240
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,720
And these temporal engines
mess up the Handbots' sensors.

241
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,560
So, where's the temporal engines?

242
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:10,240
Temporal engines held within.

243
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:11,960
Okay.

244
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:17,160
HANDBOT:
Do not be alarmed. This is a kindness.

245
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:23,120
Ha! Don't like that, do you?

246
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,320
Temporal engines. Somewhere to hide.

247
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,280
Where is everyone?

248
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,640
All right, Rory,
switch the time glass on the sonic key.

249
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,560
I'm sending a command signal
to the screwdriver.

250
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:59,280
Amy's here somewhere.
If I can just get a lock on her.

251
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:03,440
I wonder what happens
if we mix the filters?

252
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:11,960
And there they are.
40,000 time streams overlapping.

253
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,560
Red Waterfall isn't one time stream.

254
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,040
It's thousands.

255
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,440
Are they happy?

256
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:22,040
Oh, Rory, trust you to think of that.

257
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,760
I think they're happy to be alive.

258
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,320
Better than the alternative.

259
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:31,040
I come in peace.
Peace, peace, peace, peace.

260
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,720
(ELECTRONIC VOICE) I waited.

261
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,320
Sorry, what?

262
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,400
I waited for you.

263
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,040
I waited for you.

264
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,680
Amy.

265
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:51,720
Doctor, what's going on?

266
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,080
Uh...

267
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,440
Amy.

268
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:05,400
DOCTOR: I think the time stream lock
might be a bit wobbly.

269
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:08,440
RORY: No, please, please.

270
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:09,640
Duck.

271
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,080
-Oh!
-Argh!

272
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:25,120
Handbots carry a black box
in case they go offline.

273
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,920
I've changed the cause of termination
from 'hostile' to 'accidental'.

274
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:31,440
Easy to reprogram, use my sonic probe.

275
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,280
-Amy.
-Rory.

276
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,520
Why?

277
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,080
Because the only way
I've survived this long

278
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:39,880
is by making the Handbots think
I don't exist.

279
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,440
Don't touch the hands.

280
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,960
There's an aesthetic transfer
in the skin.

281
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,360
If they touch you, you go to sleep.

282
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,840
But you're still here.

283
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:49,920
You didn't save me.

284
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:58,560
But... This is the saving.
This is the us saving you.

285
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:00,760
The Doctor just got
the timing a bit out!

286
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:01,960
(MOUTHING)

287
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,680
I've been on my own here
a long, long time.

288
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,920
I've had decades
to think nice thoughts about him.

289
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Got a bit harder to stay charitable
once I entered decade four.

290
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,680
40 years? Alone?

291
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,080
36 years. Thanks.

292
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,520
No, right, I mean...

293
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:23,840
You look great. Really. Really.

294
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,160
Eyes front, soldier.

295
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,080
Still can't win, then?

296
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:32,680
In fact, I think I can now
definitely say I hate him.

297
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,160
I hate the Doctor.

298
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,960
I hate him more than
I've ever hated anyone in my life.

299
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:40,560
And you can hear it every word of this
through those ridiculous glasses,

300
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,160
can't you, raggedy man?

301
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,480
Uh, yes.

302
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,160
Putting the speakerphone on.

303
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,920
You told me to wait and I did.
A lifetime.

304
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,720
-Amy!
-You've got nothing to say to me.

305
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,400
Amy, behind you!

306
00:17:57,320 --> 00:18:00,480
Feedback knocks them out.
Learned that trick on my first day.

307
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:06,120
Okay, so we just take the Tardis back
to the right time stream, eh?

308
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,720
We can stop any of this happening.

309
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,400
DOCTOR:
We locked onto a time stream, Rory.

310
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:11,520
This is it

311
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:12,880
This is so wrong.

312
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:15,480
I got old, Rory.
What did you think was going to happen?

313
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:19,520
Hey, I don't care that you got old.
I care that we didn't grow old together.

314
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,960
Amy, come on, please.

315
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,480
Don't touch me. Don't do that.

316
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,560
It's like you're not even her.

317
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:31,160
Thirty-six years, three months,
four days of solitary confinement.

318
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,680
This facility was built
to give people a chance to live.

319
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,920
I walked in here and I died.

320
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:39,880
Did you have anything to say?
Anything, Doctor?

321
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:43,520
Where did you get a sonic screwdriver?

322
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,040
I made it. And it's a sonic probe.

323
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,120
You made a sonic screwdriver?

324
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:49,880
Probe.

325
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,040
Oh!

326
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,840
Don't worry about him. Sit down, Rory.

327
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:20,520
-You named him after me?
-Needed a bit of company.

328
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:22,920
-Oh, so, he's like your...
-Pet.

329
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:33,160
-Is it safe?
-Yeah. I disarmed it.

330
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,160
How?

331
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,960
Oh. You disarmed it.

332
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:46,960
Oh, don't get sentimental.
It's just a robot.

333
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,400
You'd have done the same.

334
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,760
I don't that I would've.

335
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,040
And there he is. The voice of God.

336
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:56,600
"Survive, because
no one's going to come for you.”

337
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:59,200
Number one lesson. You taught me that.

338
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,400
DOCTOR: Is that really all I taught you?

339
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,440
Don't you lecture me.

340
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:06,120
Blue box man flying through
time and space on whimsy.

341
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:10,040
All I've got, all I've had for 36 years
is cold, hard reality.

342
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:15,280
So, no, I don't have a sonic screwdriver
because I'm not off on a romp.

343
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:19,160
I call it what it is. A probe.
And I call my life what it is.

344
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,840
Hell.

345
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,760
Amy Pond, I'm going to put this right.
You said you learned from an interface.

346
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:28,880
Can I speak with it?

347
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:30,040
It doesn't work in here.

348
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:33,400
2:23, the garden will be clear now.

349
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:34,760
Stay or go?

350
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:39,080
Sorry, me? No, I'm coming with you.

351
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,000
Then try not to get killed,
or do, whatever.

352
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:48,680
When I first came here,

353
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:51,200
I had to trick the interface
into giving me information.

354
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,600
I've reprogrammed it now.

355
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:55,480
It will tell me anything
except how to escape.

356
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:57,200
You hacked it? That's genius.

357
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:59,440
DOCTOR: Sorry to interrupt
that beautiful moment,

358
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:01,400
but temporal engines like that
have a regulator valve,

359
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,520
has to be kept at a distance
from the main reactor

360
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:06,680
or there'd be feedback.
Interface, where's the regulator?

361
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:09,760
AUTOMATED VOICE:
The regulator valve is held within.

362
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,080
Oh, very, very, ah...

363
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,760
Interface, I need to run through
some technical specifications.

364
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:17,720
Rory, give me to Amy a minute.

365
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,320
Here you go.

366
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,160
They look ridiculous.

367
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,280
That's what I told him.

368
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:37,440
Still, anything beats a fez, eh?

369
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:38,760
(LAUGHING)

370
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:43,040
What is it?

371
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:49,200
I think that's the first time
I've laughed in 36 years.

372
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,680
I'll just, um,

373
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,720
leave you two geniuses alone.
I'll be back in a minute.

374
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,160
DOCTOR: There's still time, Amy.

375
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:10,000
There's still time to fix everything.

376
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:26,040
How can you have a door without a wall?

377
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,880
-(THUMPS)
-Oh!

378
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:35,880
Holographic wallpaper?

379
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:38,160
Oh!

380
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,840
HANDBOT:
Do not be alarmed. This is a kindness.

381
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:49,440
Rory? Rory.

382
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:50,640
(GROANING)

383
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,680
Glasses.

384
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,560
Stupid!

385
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:55,960
Oh!

386
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:59,200
-You saved me.
-Don't get used to it.

387
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,280
You've been crying.

388
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:03,400
-A little bit.
-Shut up, Rory.

389
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,560
You have, haven't you?

390
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,360
Woman with a sword. Don't push it.

391
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,680
Ha!

392
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:09,560
Okay. So, here's the plan.

393
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:12,960
Time is always a bit wibbly-wobbly
but in two streams, it's extra wobbly.

394
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:14,840
I've worked out a way to hijack
the temporal engines

395
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:18,080
and use them to fold two points
of Amy's timeline together.

396
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:20,920
We're bringing her out of the "then”
and into the "now"!

397
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,440
Amy, I just need to
borrow your brain a minute.

398
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:24,560
It won't hurt, probably.

399
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:27,880
Almost probably and then,
Amy Pond, I'm going to save you.

400
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:31,160
No!

401
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,960
Time's up. Handbots coming.

402
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,680
DOCTOR:
Amy, you've got to help us help you.

403
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:42,440
I need you to think back 36 years ago.

404
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:43,640
Amy?

405
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:45,360
Amy!

406
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:53,480
You told her to leave us a sign.

407
00:23:57,960 --> 00:24:01,320
She did and she waited.

408
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:06,920
Oh, Amy.

409
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,200
Why won't you help yourself?

410
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:11,720
He wants to rescue past me
from 36 years back,

411
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,400
which means I'll cease to exist.

412
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:15,800
Everything I've seen and done dissolves.
Time is rewritten.

413
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,920
That's...

414
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,240
That's good, isn't it?

415
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,440
I will die.

416
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:20,800
Another Amy will take my place.

417
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,480
An Amy who never got trapped
at Two-Streams,

418
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,880
an Amy who grew old with you.

419
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:25,840
And she, in 36 years, won't be me.

420
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,920
But you'll die in here!

421
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,800
Not if you take me with you.

422
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,840
You came to rescue me, so rescue me.

423
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:41,400
Leave her and take you?

424
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:45,120
We could take this Amy with us easy.

425
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:48,120
But if we do, our Amy has to wait
36 years to be rescued.

426
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:51,960
So I have to choose

427
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,840
which wife do I want?

428
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:57,400
She is me. We're both me.

429
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:59,160
You being here is wrong.

430
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,800
For a single day, an hour,
let alone a lifetime.

431
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,600
I swore to protect you.

432
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,840
I promised.

433
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,920
-Rory.
-This is your fault.

434
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:18,400
-I am so sorry, but Rory...
-No, this is your fault!

435
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:22,280
You should look at a history book
once in a while,

436
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,640
see if there's
an outbreak of plague or not.

437
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:24,880
That is not how I travel.

438
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:27,160
Then I do not want to travel with you.

439
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,640
(FEEDBACK WHINING)

440
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,600
(AMY CRYING)

441
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:47,920
DOCTOR: Rory, if the time glass is
still on, if the link's still active,

442
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:50,960
I think I can hear Amy. Our Amy.

443
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:52,800
(AMY CRYING)

444
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,800
Oh, Amy.

445
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,840
Look me in the face
and say you won't help her.

446
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,080
I will not help her.

447
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:26,840
Okay.

448
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,040
Okay.

449
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:44,600
Look me in the face and say it now.

450
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:46,000
(AMY SOBBING)

451
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:51,880
AMY: Rory? Rory, is that you?

452
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,520
Rory, where are you?

453
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:05,120
RORY: Same place as you.
Only I'm a bit ahead.

454
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:08,000
I remember this.

455
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:10,640
Who's she?
There's no one else here, but...

456
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:16,880
Me?

457
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,800
Why are we still here?

458
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:35,680
Because they leave you here.

459
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:38,680
Because they get in their Tardis
and they fly away.

460
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:39,800
No.

461
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:41,960
Rory wouldn't. Not ever.

462
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,760
Something must have stopped him.

463
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,800
You did.

464
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:49,480
Or rather, the old version of you.

465
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:52,600
The me version of you.

466
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:56,960
I refused to help them.
I won't let them save myself.

467
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,120
Why?

468
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:02,240
If you escape,
then I was never trapped here.

469
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:06,360
The last 36 years of my life rewrites
and I cease to exist.

470
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:12,280
That's why the old me
refused to help then,

471
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,840
that's why I am refusing to help now.

472
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:19,480
And that's why you'll refuse to help
when it's your turn.

473
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:23,320
And nothing you can say
will change that.

474
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,400
Three words.

475
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,840
What about Rory?

476
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:30,440
Rory.

477
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:34,640
I called my robot Rory.

478
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,840
You called your robot Rory?

479
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:41,040
Oh, so, you didn't call it The Doctor?

480
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:44,120
Or Biggles, our favourite cat?

481
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,240
Do you, um...

482
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:50,640
Do you remember that summer
when he came back to school

483
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:52,480
with that ridiculous haircut?

484
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:54,440
He said he'd been in a rock band.

485
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:58,880
Liar.

486
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:03,600
And then he had to learn
to play the guitar.

487
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:06,440
So we would know he couldn't play it.
Mmm-hmm.

488
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:16,280
All those boys chasing me.

489
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,640
But it was only ever Rory.

490
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,200
Why was that?

491
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:30,120
You know when sometimes
you meet someone

492
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,080
so beautiful,

493
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:34,200
and then you actually talk to them

494
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:36,480
and five minutes later
they're as dull as a brick?

495
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:41,200
Then there's other people,
and you meet them and you think,

496
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:42,760
"Not bad. They're okay."

497
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:46,320
And then, you get to know them

498
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:50,080
and their face just sort of

499
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,200
becomes them.

500
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:56,160
Like their personality is
written all over it.

501
00:29:56,760 --> 00:30:01,160
And they just, they turn into something
so beautiful.

502
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:06,520
BOTH: Rory is the most beautiful man
I have ever met.

503
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,000
Please,

504
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:18,560
do it for him.

505
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:19,840
Oh, you...

506
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:22,760
You're asking me to defy destiny,

507
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:25,840
causality, the nexus of time itself,
for a boy.

508
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:29,080
You're Amy.

509
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,640
He's Rory.

510
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:39,000
Oh, yes I am.

511
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:55,000
I am going to pull time apart for you.

512
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:31,080
Okay, Doctor,
Two-Streams is back on air.

513
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:32,760
Right, okay, so this is big news.

514
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:36,680
This is temporal earthquake time.
I'm officially changing my own future.

515
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,280
Hold onto your spectacles.

516
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:41,240
In my past, I saw my future self
refuse to help you.

517
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:42,880
I am now changing that future
and agreeing.

518
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:45,440
Every law of time says
that shouldn't be possible.

519
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:47,520
Yes, except sometimes knowing
your own future

520
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:48,960
is what enables you to change it.

521
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:51,000
Especially if you're bloody-minded,
contradictory

522
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:52,720
and completely unpredictable.

523
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,440
So, basically, if you're Amy, then.

524
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:58,320
Yes, if anyone could defeat pre-destiny,
it's your wife.

525
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:01,920
It's not about what I'm doing,
it's about who I'm doing it for.

526
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,240
I am trusting you
to watch my back, Rory.

527
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:07,520
Always.

528
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:10,760
-You and me, always.
-Because here is the deal.

529
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:14,720
You take me, too, in the Tardis.

530
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:17,200
Me, too.

531
